{"word":"θράσσω","slug":"θράσσω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>θράσσω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:contracted, contraction'>contr.</a> from <a href='S:ταράσσω'><el>ταράσσω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to trouble, disquiet</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to destroy, ruin</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}